itemDescription: ran the 110M high hurdles for Great Britain in the 1948 London Olympics

wikipedia_page.main: Raymond Barkway (1924–1956) ran the 110M high hurdles for Great Britain in the 1948 London Olympics. He was killed in a plane crash he was piloting aged only 32 years old.
